citation: Proclamation under the Police Offences Amendment (Clamping) Act 2009 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Police Offences Amendment (Clamping) Act 2009

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2 of the Police Offences Amendment (Clamping) Act 2009 fix 11 December 2009 as the day on which that Act commences.

30 November 2009

PETER G. UNDERWOOD

Governor

By His Excellency's Command,

J. G. COX

Minister for Police and Emergency Management

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 9 December 2009

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Police and Emergency Management.
